title: Working with Russia in Syria is dicey prospect for U.S.
text:
23 Working with Russia in Syria is dicey prospect for U.S. 
Army Times: The Pentagon may soon have to decide whether to begin detailed military coordination with Russia as the former Cold War adversary is poised to begin its own combat air operations over the multisided civil war in Syria.Russia reportedly has assembled dozens of attack aircraft at an air base in Latakia, on Syria's Mediterranean coast. The fleet includes 12 Sukhoi SU-24 attack aircraft and another 12 SU-25 ground attack aircraft, U.S. officials said
